      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between automated blogging tools and SEO tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Generic automated blogging tools focus on producing content volume. SEO-focused tools add keyword research, SERP analysis, on-page optimization, and content scoring. The difference is whether the content is built to rank, not just to exist. Every tool on this list treats SEO as a primary function, not an add-on.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can automated blogging tools produce content that actually ranks?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes, when the tool includes SERP analysis, keyword targeting, and on-page optimization. Tools like theStacc, Surfer SEO, and Frase generate content calibrated to what Google already rewards for a given keyword. Content still benefits from topical authority on your domain. Tools that skip SERP analysis produce content that needs more manual SEO work to compete.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do I still need an SEO expert if I use these tools?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">For basic SEO blogging — targeting informational keywords, publishing consistently, building internal links — these tools handle the fundamentals. For competitive keywords, technical SEO, backlink strategy, and site architecture, you'll still benefit from SEO expertise. The tools cover content production and on-page optimization, not the full SEO discipline.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much do automated SEO blogging tools cost?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Prices range from $9/month (Koala.sh) to $999/month (Byword at scale). Most full-featured tools cost $49–$149/month. theStacc publishes 30 SEO articles for $99/month — $3.30 per article. Compare that to $150–$300 per article from freelance SEO writers or $250–$500 per article from agencies.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Which tool is best for local business SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
